verses.roman:
śrī-jagannāthera dekhe śrī-mukha-kamala
tāhāra upara sundara nayana-yugala

synonyms: śrī-jagannāthera—of Lord Jagannātha; dekhe—sees; śrī-mukha-kamala—the lotuslike face; tāhāra upara—upon this; sundara—beautiful; nayana-yugala—a pair of eyes.
translation: Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu looked upon the beautiful lotuslike face and eyes of Lord Jagannātha.
